ible than the notion NASA faked the moon landings.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Starti=
ng there, the <i>Post </i>compiled a top 10 list of statements, dating back=
 to March, that =E2=80=9Ceven by Trump=E2=80=99s own conspiratorial and fal=
sehood-laden standards =E2=80=A6 pushed the envelope in new
and astonishing ways.=E2=80=9D Those professionally obliged to be close stu=
dents of the Trump oeuvre (heaven help us) might quibble with this or that =
item in the <i>Post</i>=E2=80=99s chrestomathy. But by and large it=E2=80=
=99s a solid highlight reel of Trump=E2=80=99s recent fabrications, fantasi=
es, and/or delusions: that Biden authorized the F.B.I. to kill him when it =
raided Mar-a-Lago and now plans to crash the Democratic convention and recl=
aim his party=E2=80=99s nomination; that Trump once shared a white-knuckle =
