arris, his long-ago paramour; that the crowd at Trump=E2=80=99s rally on th=
e Washington Mall on January 6 was bigger than the throng in attendance at =
<b>M.L.K.</b>=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9CI Have a Dream=E2=80=9D speech in 1963; an=
d that Harris only recently =E2=80=9Chappened to turn Black.=E2=80=9D<br/><=
br/>Now, it=E2=80=99s fair enough to say that compulsive ranting, hot-eyed =
raving, and pathological mendacity are no novelty for Trump. In his time on=
 the national
stage, these tendencies have been the most consistent aspects of his public=
 persona. But something new <i>has </i>occurred since Biden=E2=80=99s decis=
ion to stand down and Harris=E2=80=99s rocket-ride ascent began: The flood =
of brain-melting gibberish pouring out of Trump=E2=80=99s mouth (or from th=
e tips of those itty-bitty cocktail sausages he types with) has escalated a=
nd intensified to a remarkable degree. Of the 10 items on the <i>Post</i>=
=E2=80=99s list, <i>seven </i>of them were less than a month old=E2=80=94an=
d in the days after the piece was published, Trump held several more public=
 events, each producing at least one or two more instances of top 10-worthy=
 confusion, dissociation, incoherent muttering, infantile squawking, or sta=
ndard-issue unfathomable lunacy.<br/><br/>Political journalism has always s=
truggled to fully capture or cope with Trump when he=E2=80=99s lost the plo=
t=E2=80=94and it=E2=80=99s struggling mightily now. The standard recourse i=
s to embrace euphemism: to say that Harris=E2=80=99s rise has
=E2=80=9Crattled=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cdisoriented=E2=80=9D Trump or =E2=80=
=9Cknocked him off his game,=E2=80=9D that he=E2=80=99s failing to =E2=80=
=9Cdrive a consistent message,=E2=80=9D that he=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cunfocuse=
d=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cundisciplined.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>But if we=E2=80=99r=
e honest about Trump=E2=80=99s public behavior over the past month, there=
=E2=80=99s no getting around the fact that the words and phrases above aren=
=E2=80=99t merely euphemisms or modestly inaccurate descriptions of his per=
formances on the stump. These weasel words and phrases are well-intentioned=
 but ultimately misleading bullshit. The Trump on display on the campaign t=
rail in the past month isn=E2=80=99t disoriented, unfocused, or undisciplin=
ed=E2=80=94he=E2=80=99s dotty, doddering, demented, possibly deranged, and =
<i>clearly </i>disturbed.<br/><br/>Which is the point that Trump-watchers f=
ar more obsessive than me=E2=80=94coming from widely varying ideological an=
d temperamental orientations=E2=80=94are now making in unison. As <b>Ezra K=
lein </b>put it to me on my podcast last week, =E2=80=9Cthe strain of Harri=
s=E2=80=9D=E2=80=94the
attention she=E2=80=99s getting, the size of her crowds, the way her elevat=
ion has upended Trump=E2=80=99s expectations about the race and how it was =
destined to play out=E2=80=94 =E2=80=9Chas broken him.=E2=80=9D Or, as <b>G=
eorge Conway</b> declared in the wake of his fake-crowd posts, =E2=80=9CHe=
=E2=80=99s done. His brain is fried.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Stating the obvious =
for the record: Neither George, Ezra, nor I are doctors or have had any spe=
cialized training that qualifies us to diagnose Donald Trump. Nor do many o=
f the growing number of observers who contend that Trump is, at a minimum, =
exhibiting signs of a notable decline in mental acuity, or, more floridly, =
that he is in the midst of what Chait has called a =E2=80=9Cmental health d=
eath spiral.=E2=80=9D (Though if you want to read a fascinating examination=
 of Trump=E2=80=99s apparent cognitive decline that quotes numerous experts=
 in various relevant scientific fields, you should check out <u><a href=3D"=
https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dSYUF=
2bkhWdHpVc3g0X1hlQzRjZz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc3RhdG5ld3MuY29tLzIwMj=
QvMDgvMDcvdHJ1bXAtbWVudGFsLWhlYWx0aC1saW5ndWlzdGljLWFuYWx5c2lzLXN1Z2dlc3RzL=
XBvdGVudGlhbC1jb2duaXRpdmUtZGVjbGluZS1leHBlcnRzLXNheS8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPVRo=
ZStCZXN0KyUyNitUaGUrQnJpZ2h0ZXN0Ky0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4OCUyRjE4JTJGMjQlMjl=
cdTAwMjZ1dG1fY29udGVudD1UaGUrQmVzdCslMjYrVGhlK0JyaWdodGVzdCstK1NVQlNDUklCRV=
JTKyUyODclMkYyNCUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25cdTAwMjZ1d=
G1fc291cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwi=
aW50ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjo5OTk1NjN9/089484f888=
dd82f7183f1326e8cf74f1dce4fe6eee7285efaa523215e5f0133f" style=3D"color:#d40=
000;text-decoration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">this piece</a></u>=
 in STAT News.)<br/><br/>But you don=E2=80=99t need to be a doctor to recog=
nize that Trump is plainly too impaired to be president, just as the vast m=
ajority of voters (including a majority of Democrats) didn=E2=80=99t requir=
e a medical license to decide that Biden wasn=E2=80=99t fit for another fou=
r-year term. They could confidently come to that conclusion because virtual=
ly all of them had personal experience dealing with one or more octogenaria=
n or septuagenarian family members who=E2=80=99d taken the sad but inescapa=
ble turn toward age-related diminishment. <br/><br/>I hear some of you
saying, or potentially screaming, that while Trump=E2=80=99s voyage into th=
at realm may have picked up speed of late, his cognitive state has been far=
 from robust for a very long time. And hey, guess what, I agree with you, a=
nd have been saying on television for <i>years </i>that Trump often sounded=
 like a guy you=E2=80=99d come across in the park feeding stale bread to th=
e pigeons=E2=80=94and that if he were your uncle, you=E2=80=99d be actively=
 on the hunt for a decent assisted living facility. But in the political/me=
dia worlds as they currently exist=E2=80=94and not as they <i>should </i>be=
=E2=80=94Trump benefited enormously from having Biden opposite him on the p=
residential campaign split screen.<br/><br/>=E2=80=9CTrump has big lunatic =
energy=E2=80=9D is how the #NeverTrump focus group impresario <b>Sarah</b> =
<b>Longwell</b> explained it to me one day. =E2=80=9CAnd for a lot of voter=
s, when the split screen was Joe Biden, they were gonna take big lunatic en=
ergy over frail energy every time.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>But with Biden out of
the picture, Trump finds himself facing a far less forgiving split screen=
=E2=80=94one, indeed, made actively punishing by Harris=E2=80=99s presence,=
 which throws his cognitive decline (and psychological instability and emot=
ional precariousness, for good measure) into increasingly stark relief. How=
 stark? So stark that, slowly but surely, the national press is starting to=
 talk about Trump the way it once talked about the guy who=E2=80=99ll be sp=
eaking in Chicago tomorrow night. <br/><br/>To wit: =E2=80=9CFor the first =
time this week I thought people were wondering about the impact of Mr. Trum=
p=E2=80=99s age,=E2=80=9D <b>Peggy</b> <b>Noonan</b> wrote in her column af=
ter the former president=E2=80=99s unhinged press conference at Mar-a-Lago=
=E2=80=94the one where he somehow confused Willie Brown with both <b>Jerry =
Brown</b> and an African American Democratic city councilman from Los Angel=
es, just as a few months ago he somehow confused <b>Nikki</b> <b>Haley</b> =
and <b>Nancy</b> <b>Pelosi</b>. =E2=80=9CHe is 78. He hasn=E2=80=99t been
able to focus, make his case. Is he, in another irony of 2024, turning into=
 Joe Biden?=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Put aside the fact that, however many miles a=
n hour Biden has lost from his fast ball, on his worst day he was never an =
inveterate, reflexive, serial liar or peddler of pernicious and utterly bat=
shit conspiracy theories, etcetera. The real import of Noonan=E2=80=99s ana=
logy is that Biden=E2=80=99s departure from the race may have bequeathed a =
huge political gift to his successor and his party that none of them saw co=
ming at all: not just making Trump the old man on the field but unleashing =
the same dynamic on him that proved to be Biden=E2=80=99s undoing=E2=80=94a=
 dynamic you can bet the Harris campaign is already laboring, just below th=
e water line, to exploit.<br/><br/>All of which is to say, it=E2=80=99s ent=
irely possible that Trump may finally be about to discover what it=E2=80=99=
s like to be on the receiving end of a kind and degree of scrutiny regardin=
g his age and mental fitness that he and his allies did
much to foment and aim at Biden. And if we=E2=80=99ve learned nothing else =
about Trump since Harris became his didn=E2=80=99t-see-that-coming opponent=
, it=E2=80=99s that, like many elderly gentlemen with poor memories, ingrai=
ned habits, and long-festering manias, he tends to get a touch cranky if so=
meone or something disrupts his routine.<br/></td>
